snippet.textDisplay: Shafqat g tussi kamal ho, lots of love and respect for you.. that's your khandani gaeyqi and practice, which a lot may not understand., I adore ahmed too, honestly i mean it.. i still listen to his TU JO NAHI.. I said to my friends back in the days when his debut song came this singer will go long way.. and I love his voice and classical skills BUT when it comes to patiala people.. no sorry no match.. the difference is clear.. when Shafqat sings.. well all lines but my favourite one mere irade jo tootey.. NOTICE how smooth his voice picks up like a new honda civic lol, i mean so smooth that no single word is said in a higher or lower pitch.. all flow smoothly, and how magnificently he ends the line with "Pata ye CHALAAAAA..... aiiiiiii haiiiiiiiii.... maza agya... I notice to the pitch and variations in his voice a lot and love them.. whilst Ahmed, he sings with a lot of variations..though I do agree Ahmed naturally has a beautiful voice but not the practice of Shafqat.. don't forget who's son Shafqat is, who were his uncles and brother.. ALL LEGENDS.. , so sorry but i strongly DISAGREE to those who said Ahmed has done better in this.. perhaps you don;t understand music (as much as I do at least LOL). Peace and Azadi mubarak to All PAKISTANI AWAM.. PAKISTAN ZINDABAD.
